<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id79672d1b-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0" identifier="/us/usc/t15/s1157"><num value="1157">§ 1157.</num><heading> Relation to other provisions</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in this chapter shall be construed to repeal or amend any other legislation pertaining to the Department of Commerce or its component offices or bureaus.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id79672d1c-552d-11f1-9071-ff305b7c3ff0">(<ref href="/us/act/1950-09-09/ch936/s7">Sept. 9, 1950, ch. 936, § 7</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/64/824">64 Stat. 824</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
